## Automated Experimental Sweeps

### Available Experiments

|Type            |Variable         |Range        |Purpose                    |
|----------------|-----------------|-------------|---------------------------|
|Γ Scan          |Boundary position|0 → 0.6      |Map field coupling vs depth|
|Energy          |Electron energy  |200 → 2000 eV|Test wavelength dependence |
|Torsion Coupling|ε parameter      |0.1 → 2.0    |Sensitivity analysis       |
|Mass Scaling    |BH mass          |1 → 100 M☉   |Geometric scaling laws     |

### Data Output

Each sweep generates:

- **Framework identifier** (TEGR vs GR)
- **Parameter trajectory** (Γ, E, etc.)
- **Field evolution** (θ or R at each step)
- **Observable changes** (Δχ², contrast, etc.)
- **Convergence metrics** (PDE stability)

